race.description: First National Charles King & Co Cohuna Mdn Plate
race.comment: CASTLEFIELD FLYER (4) showed promise on debut then went for a break. Was solid fresh and strips fitter for this easier assignment. Expected to go close. MACHINE MAN (11) was solid on debut when finishing midfield in a much tougher maiden. Sure to be improved on that run and has a low draw in this. One of the main chances. HAS HE GOT IT (2) turned in a brave effort last time when he attempted to make all but was claimed late and finished third over 1150m at Leeton. Speedy galloper who looks the leading and will be in this for a long way. SARAYA (8) is a 14 starts maiden having first try here but has placed only try this trip. Last appeared when she finished third over 1300m at Jerilderie on September 27. Has shown some ability and gets chance to fire here.
